President Obama spoke with President Ashraf Ghani of Afghanistan and Chief Executive Officer Dr. Abdullah Abdullah via video conference. They discussed the need for Afghanistan to form an inclusive national unity government and expressed their commitment to a strengthened U.S.-Afghan strategic partnership. They also talked about the efforts of the Afghan National Security Forces to improve security and the importance of countering extremist threats. President Obama praised President Ghani and Dr. Abdullah for their leadership in promoting an Afghan peace process and their initiative to improve relations with Pakistan.